  "text": "The GDScript VM security boundary spans two main areas. (1) The bytecode interpreter lives in gdscript_vm.cpp with GDScriptFunction::call() implementing the opcode dispatch loop (using computed-goto OPCODE_SWITCH macro). GDScriptFunction is declared in gdscript_function.h with call-frame/stack management (_stack_size, etc.). The byte-code generator (gdscript_byte_codegen.h/cpp) emits the opcodes the VM executes. (2) The Object method dispatch chain: Object::callp() in core/object/object.cpp first checks the script instance (ScriptInstance::callp virtual, implemented by GDScriptInstance::callp in gdscript.cpp), then falls back to ClassDB-registered methods via MethodBind (class_db.h/cpp, method_bind.h/cpp). ClassDB controls which engine APIs are exposed to scripts via bind_method_custom and register_class. The @tool annotation permission check is in gdscript_parser.cpp (tool_annotation), with GDScript::is_tool() gating whether scripts run in-editor. The ScriptInstance interface (script_instance.h) and ScriptLanguage base (script_language.h) define the abstract boundary between scripts and the engine.",
